07:06.613 --> 07:08.379
And for every wife
who's wanted to throw

07:08.380 --> 07:11.945
sharp things at her husband,
I say thank you.

07:11.946 --> 07:14.045
I love you.
[cheers and applause]

07:14.046 --> 07:15.679
When you turned around
and you had the knives

07:15.680 --> 07:18.645
in your hand, there was, like,
something kind of crazy

07:18.646 --> 07:21.779
in your eyes that I was like,
"I get it.

07:21.780 --> 07:23.645
This is why he fell
in love with you."

07:23.646 --> 07:25.645
[laughter]
Thank you. Thank you.

07:25.646 --> 07:27.379
I was thinking,
you know what,

07:27.380 --> 07:28.879
this is a great show.

07:28.880 --> 07:31.645
When you get bad singers,
rather than buzzing them,

07:31.646 --> 07:33.212
we throw knives at them.

07:33.213 --> 07:35.312
Are you saying I'm--are
you saying I'm a bad singer?

07:35.313 --> 07:37.512
I mean, I've been studying
opera since I'm a child.

07:37.513 --> 07:39.112
What didn't you like
about my voice?

07:39.113 --> 07:40.612
Your voice.

07:40.613 --> 07:42.245
[audience boos]
Really? Okay.

07:42.246 --> 07:44.012
No.

07:44.013 --> 07:45.779
Well, look,
there are four of us.

07:45.780 --> 07:47.579
