How do you feel?
Uh, I'm humbled,

28:08.980 --> 28:11.145
and I'm honored that,
you know,

28:11.146 --> 28:13.245
you guys took the time
to give me another chance,

28:13.246 --> 28:16.645
and I thrive under pressure
and I love trying to adapt

28:16.646 --> 28:19.679
and overcome,
and thank you for the chance.

28:19.680 --> 28:23.212
So right there, that's
where I felt your authenticity,

28:23.213 --> 28:25.879
and that goes a long way.

28:25.880 --> 28:27.812
Well done.
Thank you.

28:27.813 --> 28:30.479
[cheers and applause]

28:30.480 --> 28:31.612
Howie.

28:31.613 --> 28:33.045
I think that
you're really good,

28:33.046 --> 28:34.379
and you've got
a really good voice.

28:34.380 --> 28:36.312
Taking all the direction
from Simon

28:36.313 --> 28:37.812
and listening to everybody,

28:37.813 --> 28:40.712
you stepped it up ten levels
as far as I'm concerned.

28:40.713 --> 28:41.879
[cheers and applause]

28:41.880 --> 28:43.312
Gabrielle?

28:43.313 --> 28:45.945
Okay, we literally threw
everything at this young man

28:45.946 --> 28:47.312
plus the kitchen sink.

28:47.313 --> 28:49.145
He went backstage,

28:49.146 --> 28:51.012
learned a song
he's never heard before,

28:51.013 --> 28:54.445
played before, nothing,
and the guitar and sang it,

28:54.446 --> 28:57.845
and came out here and just
blew us all away.

28:57.846 --> 29:00.779
[cheers and applause]
Perspective.

29:00.780 --> 29:03.112
We don't each other well,
Lamont, but I respect you

29:03.113 --> 29:04.812
for doing what you did.

29:04.813 --> 29:06.545
I think there is a wall
in front of you,

29:06.546 --> 29:08.479
which is the fear of failure,

29:08.480 --> 29:10.479
and I think you've got to
let yourself go a little bit,

29:10.480 --> 29:12.145
and there's nothing wrong
about looking emotional

29:12.146 --> 29:13.979
or happy or sad.

29:13.980 --> 29:15.512
Yes, yes.

29:15.513 --> 29:18.945
And, you know, the cracking
of the egg is a good analogy.

29:18.946 --> 29:21.112
You know, it's like
I know what it's like

29:21.113 --> 29:22.612
when it's frustrating
and you get criticized,

29:22.613 --> 29:23.779
and you think you're right,

29:23.780 --> 29:25.012
but something's
getting in the way,

29:25.013 --> 29:26.945
and you get frustrated,
and then sometimes

29:26.946 --> 29:28.345
someone gives you
a little bit of advice

29:28.346 --> 29:29.845
and it opens the door.

29:29.846 --> 29:31.479
I think the door has just
opened for you here.

29:31.480 --> 29:32.912
Yeah.
I do.

29:32.913 --> 29:35.379
Those frustrations are when
breakthroughs happen.

29:35.380 --> 29:36.979
Yeah.
Thank you.

29:36.980 --> 29:38.312
And to the audience,
I apologize.

29:38.313 --> 29:41.079
You have every right to clap.
[laughter]

29:41.080 --> 29:43.545
I just, uh--
[cheers and applause]

29:43.546 --> 29:45.245
It was my own thing here.

29:45.246 --> 29:46.712
[laughs] I like you.

29:46.713 --> 29:48.912
Okay, we're gonna vote.
Howie, yes or no?

29:48.913 --> 29:51.045
Based on what you did
at the beginning

29:51.046 --> 29:54.412
and then how you improved,
I'm giving you a yes.

29:54.413 --> 29:55.845
Gabrielle.

29:55.846 --> 29:57.679
I mean, you made a believer
out of all of us, yes.

29:57.680 --> 29:59.612
Thank you, thank you,
thank you, thank you.

29:59.613 --> 30:00.979
Julianne.
I see it.

30:00.980 --> 30:03.412
I feel it in you.
I want more.

30:03.413 --> 30:05.379
Yes.
Thank you.

30:05.380 --> 30:06.812
Thank you, thank you.

30:06.813 --> 30:09.579
Lamont, you know what,
we all have our ups and downs.

30:09.580 --> 30:11.845
At least you had the guts
and the respect

30:11.846 --> 30:13.145
for doing
what you've just done,

30:13.146 --> 30:14.712
and I'm really happy
that worked out for you.

30:14.713 --> 30:17.245
And you know what, let's make
the next one even better.

30:17.246 --> 30:19.545
So it's four yeses.
Thank you, thank you.

30:19.546 --> 30:21.512
Thank you,
thank you, thank you.

30:21.513 --> 30:23.112
[cheers and applause]

30:23.113 --> 30:25.212
Thank you so much.

30:25.213 --> 30:27.545
♪ It isn't in my blood ♪

30:27.546 --> 30:34.412
♪ ♪

30:34.413 --> 30:36.279
There's something
about him.

30:36.280 --> 30:38.312
It's he's complex.

30:38.313 --> 30:40.412
That's why he's interesting.

30:40.413 --> 30:42.179
I can't wait to see more.
I can't wait to hear more.

30:42.180 --> 30:44.245
Bro, you a star.
Thanks.

30:44.246 --> 30:46.879
[laughs]

30:46.880 --> 30:49.612
You're just a star.
It was so good.

30:49.613 --> 30:52.445
I was completely mesmerized.

30:52.446 --> 30:54.112
My heart.

30:54.113 --> 30:58.045
You are absolutely fantastic.

30:58.046 --> 31:00.146
[cheers and applause]

31:04.346 --> 31:04.380
.

31:05.813 --> 31:06.246
["Oh Happy Day" plays]

31:07.713 --> 31:09.545
♪ Oh happy day ♪

31:09.546 --> 31:14.079
I feel like today is gonna
be the chance of a lifetime,

31:14.080 --> 31:16.512
and it makes me feel alive.

31:16.513 --> 31:18.745
♪ When Jesus washed ♪

31:18.746 --> 31:20.479
When I step out
on this stage,

31:20.480 --> 31:22.879
this is my chance
and my opportunity

31:22.880 --> 31:25.645
to really make my dreams
come to life.

31:25.646 --> 31:27.412
[echoing]
to life... to life... to life...

31:27.413 --> 31:29.146
[rumbling, birds caw]

31:34.046 --> 31:37.045
[Carl Orff's "O Fortuna"]

31:37.046 --> 31:44.146
♪ ♪

31:47.213 --> 31:48.879
My name is Death.

31:48.880 --> 31:51.979
I am 2.4 billion years old,

31:51.980 --> 31:55.645
and I live with my dog,
Gordon, in California.

31:55.646 --> 31:57.079
[Georges Bizet's
"Carmen Suite No. 2 Habanera"]

31:57.080 --> 31:58.512
My dad is God.

31:58.513 --> 32:00.212
He's kind of a big shot.

32:00.213 --> 32:02.179
My mom is Mother Nature.

32:02.180 --> 32:04.179
She's very nurturing.

32:04.180 --> 32:08.412
Mom and Dad got a divorce when
I was 14 million years old,

32:08.413 --> 32:11.145
which is a tough age.

32:11.146 --> 32:14.112
Reaping is definitely
not the easiest job,

32:14.113 --> 32:15.845
but there are some perks.

32:15.846 --> 32:17.745
You know, I do get
to make my own schedule,

32:17.746 --> 32:20.912
and I've gotten to meet
every creative person

32:20.913 --> 32:22.579
that I've ever admired ever.

32:22.580 --> 32:23.879
The bad part is that they're

32:23.880 --> 32:26.145
usually not very happy
to see me.

32:26.146 --> 32:29.045
I've heard from all these
people about how great life is,

32:29.046 --> 32:30.579
and, you know,
I just want a piece of that,

32:30.580 --> 32:32.212
so once I took human form,

32:32.213 --> 32:34.345
there were three things
I had to do.

32:34.346 --> 32:36.445
I wanted to take
an improv class,

32:36.446 --> 32:38.845
get into standup comedy,

32:38.846 --> 32:40.212
and get a dog.

32:40.213 --> 32:43.412
I haven't been doing standup
for that long.

32:43.413 --> 32:45.745
The worst show ever,
I was at a bar,

32:45.746 --> 32:47.279
somebody heckled me.

32:47.280 --> 32:50.212
Reaping audience
members mid-show

32:50.213 --> 32:52.912
tends to kill the vibe.

32:52.913 --> 32:56.345
I'm like a really nice guy
when you get to know me.

32:56.346 --> 32:59.512
"America's Got Talent"
is a way to show America

32:59.513 --> 33:02.079
that there's more to me
than just reaping

33:02.080 --> 33:04.645
everything that you love.

33:04.646 --> 33:05.845
♪ ♪

33:05.846 --> 33:07.045
Oh, whoa!

33:07.046 --> 33:09.079
Here we go, folks.
Take your seats.

33:09.080 --> 33:11.145
It is so cold in here now.

33:11.146 --> 33:13.212
Uh, show 'em what you got.

33:13.213 --> 33:14.579
[indistinct]
Okay, okay.

33:14.580 --> 33:16.279
Oh, did that mean something?
I didn't mean nothing.

33:16.280 --> 33:18.612
No, I'm off the clock.
Okay, good, good.

33:18.613 --> 33:20.512
Go on out here.

33:20.513 --> 33:23.379
♪ ♪

33:23.380 --> 33:24.445
Oh, God!

33:24.446 --> 33:25.979
[scattered cheers]

33:25.980 --> 33:27.612
Oh.

33:27.613 --> 33:29.612
♪ ♪

33:29.613 --> 33:31.745
Death.
A little scary.

33:31.746 --> 33:36.112
♪ ♪

33:36.113 --> 33:38.445
Okay.

33:38.446 --> 33:40.779
All right, uh...
[chuckles]

33:40.780 --> 33:43.712
Let's start with welcome,

33:43.713 --> 33:46.580
and would you like to tell me
who you are, please?

33:48.013 --> 33:49.912
Death.

33:49.913 --> 33:51.145
[scattered cheers and laughter]

33:51.146 --> 33:52.779
Uh-oh, uh-oh.

33:52.780 --> 33:55.345
Why are you here, Death?

33:55.346 --> 33:57.512
I'm going to be performing

33:57.513 --> 33:59.379
standup comedy.

33:59.380 --> 34:01.245
[laughter]

34:01.246 --> 34:04.379
Okay, and can I ask you
where you're from, Death?

34:04.380 --> 34:06.779
I am from...

34:06.780 --> 34:10.545
the swirl of oblivion that
will one day swallow us all.

34:12.179 --> 34:14.478
Currently, I rent
a one-bedroom in Burbank.

34:14.480 --> 34:16.679
[laughter]

34:18.146 --> 34:21.212
Okay, well, I think
I know where this is going,

34:21.213 --> 34:23.012
so good luck.

34:23.013 --> 34:25.080
Thank you.

34:29.480 --> 34:31.612
They say...

34:31.612 --> 34:36.245
the only guarantees in life
are death and taxes.

34:36.246 --> 34:40.012
But if you walk around all
summer in a thick, black cloak,

34:40.013 --> 34:42.980
thigh chafing is also
gonna happen.

34:52.045 --> 34:54.012
[buzzer]

34:54.013 --> 34:55.245
[cheers and applause]

34:55.246 --> 34:56.978
[Scott Joplin's
"The Entertainer"]

34:56.980 --> 35:00.512
Ohh.

35:00.513 --> 35:04.745
Anyone who says
you can't cheat death

35:04.746 --> 35:07.679
hasn't met my ex-girlfriend.

35:07.680 --> 35:09.612
[booing]

35:09.613 --> 35:10.679
[buzzer]

35:10.680 --> 35:12.712
So bad.

35:12.713 --> 35:14.012
♪ ♪

35:14.013 --> 35:16.812
It's so bad, it's good.

35:16.813 --> 35:18.645
[audience shouting]

35:18.646 --> 35:22.579
♪ ♪

35:22.580 --> 35:25.812
I've been dating recently.

35:25.813 --> 35:28.745
It's tough.

35:28.746 --> 35:30.512
I get ghosted a lot.

35:30.513 --> 35:32.412
What?
[buzzer]

35:32.413 --> 35:35.312
♪ ♪

35:35.313 --> 35:38.712
I'm going to tell a relatable
dating anecdote now.

35:38.713 --> 35:40.712
♪ ♪

35:40.713 --> 35:44.312
Have you ever been on a date
and it's going well,

35:44.313 --> 35:46.479
and you go back to her place

35:46.480 --> 35:49.045
and then you remember
you have to kill her cat?

35:49.046 --> 35:51.112
[buzzer]

35:51.113 --> 35:53.513
[cheers and applause]

35:57.080 --> 35:59.279
He died onstage.

35:59.280 --> 36:01.112
Oh, you know what, Death,

36:01.113 --> 36:03.479
you're probably
gonna like this,

36:03.480 --> 36:05.379
but we hate you.

36:05.380 --> 36:06.845
♪ That's life ♪

36:06.846 --> 36:08.345
What do you think, Julianne?

36:08.346 --> 36:10.512
What was that?

36:10.513 --> 36:13.145
I'm looking for longevity,
not really death.

36:13.146 --> 36:14.612
♪ ♪

36:14.613 --> 36:17.079
Howie.
It was horribly funny

36:17.080 --> 36:20.312
because sometimes
you'll hold for laughter

36:20.313 --> 36:21.612
or hold for applause.

36:21.613 --> 36:23.679
You hold for Xes.

36:23.680 --> 36:26.645
And I'll tell you, tomorrow
morning when you're on the bus,

36:26.646 --> 36:28.979
you are gonna be recognized.

36:28.980 --> 36:31.279
[laughter]

36:31.280 --> 36:33.279
Anything you want to add,
Gabrielle?

36:33.280 --> 36:35.612
As a makeup tutorial,

36:35.613 --> 36:39.579
I'm here for the smoky eye
and the chiseled contour.

36:39.580 --> 36:40.812
Thank you.

36:40.813 --> 36:43.845
But, um, I do agree
with the criticism.

36:43.846 --> 36:46.512
Not for me.
Okay, we're gonna vote.

36:46.513 --> 36:48.379
Howie?

36:48.380 --> 36:50.012
No.
Gabrielle?

36:50.013 --> 36:51.612
Um, that's gonna be
a no for me.

36:51.613 --> 36:53.745
Julianne?
I didn't get it.

36:53.746 --> 36:56.312
So I'm gonna say no.
It's four nos.

36:56.313 --> 36:58.245
Thank you.

36:58.246 --> 37:00.145
♪ That's life,
that's life ♪

37:00.146 --> 37:03.679
♪ That's life
and I can't deny it ♪

37:03.680 --> 37:05.879
Watching him was funnier
than him.

37:05.880 --> 37:07.645
Yeah, but sometimes
when it's going bad,

37:07.646 --> 37:08.779
it's almost funnier.

37:08.780 --> 37:11.579
I'll be seeing Simon Cowell
later tonight.

37:11.580 --> 37:12.945
But you like me, right?

37:12.946 --> 37:14.779
You're cool.
Oh, thank you.

37:14.780 --> 37:16.112
Thank you.
Love the suit.

37:16.113 --> 37:17.679
Oh, thank you so much.

37:17.680 --> 37:19.479
I don't think I could have
taken that much longer.

37:19.480 --> 37:23.045
Oh, lord, oh, lord.

37:23.046 --> 37:26.512
♪ In a big ball and die ♪

37:26.513 --> 37:28.212
[maniacal laughter]

37:28.213 --> 37:29.579
[thunder rumbles]

37:29.580 --> 37:32.379
[birds caw]

37:32.380 --> 37:34.779
You still have time
to submit your design

37:34.780 --> 37:36.412
for the Dunkin' judges' cups.

37:36.413 --> 37:39.812
Head over to
NBC.com/designacup

37:39.813 --> 37:42.945
to create and submit
your very own design.

37:42.946 --> 37:46.312
If you win, you'll get Dunkin'
coffee for an entire year,

37:46.313 --> 37:49.712
and your cup will be featured
on the judges' desk.

37:49.713 --> 37:51.412
We'll even fly you
out to Hollywood

37:51.413 --> 37:53.479
to come see it live on "AGT."

37:53.480 --> 37:55.546
Good luck.

38:00.313 --> 38:00.346
.

38:02.146 --> 38:03.046
The show's called

38:02.613 --> 38:03.046
"America's Got Talent,"

38:04.046 --> 38:05.412
but actually we've been
very fortunate

38:05.413 --> 38:09.412
that people from all over
the world trust this stage,

38:09.413 --> 38:12.945
and they have the opportunity
to change their life.

38:12.946 --> 38:16.612
I still don't believe that
we are finally in America.

38:16.613 --> 38:18.545
We traveled so far
to get here.

38:18.546 --> 38:20.612
It has been a long journey.

38:20.613 --> 38:23.379
This is our chance
to live the American dream.

38:23.380 --> 38:26.245
And today, today
your lives can change.

38:26.246 --> 38:27.845
Who's next?

38:27.846 --> 38:29.612
I'm gonna guess a choir.

38:29.613 --> 38:30.945
Yeah.
Love choirs.

38:30.946 --> 38:32.645
I know, me too.

38:32.646 --> 38:35.945
[cheers and applause]

38:35.946 --> 38:37.812
Hi, guys.

38:37.813 --> 38:44.179
♪ ♪

38:44.180 --> 38:46.312
What is the name
of this group?

38:46.313 --> 38:48.279
Our name is
the Ndlovu Youth Choir,

38:48.280 --> 38:52.045
and we are all the way
from Limpopo in South Africa.

38:52.046 --> 38:53.779
Oh, you're from South Africa?
Wow!

38:53.780 --> 38:55.979
My name's Ralf Schmit.
I'm the conductor.

38:55.980 --> 38:57.012
You're the conductor.

38:57.013 --> 38:58.379
How long have you
been doing it?

38:58.380 --> 38:59.812
We've been together
for ten years.

38:59.813 --> 39:02.245
Wow.
Hi, hi.

39:02.246 --> 39:03.979
Hi.
What's your name?

39:03.980 --> 39:05.579
My name is [indistinct].

39:05.580 --> 39:07.312
Is this your first time
in America?

39:07.313 --> 39:08.712
Yes, this is my first time
in America.

39:08.713 --> 39:11.645
Hello, America!
[cheers and applause]

39:11.646 --> 39:13.045
And what does this
mean to you?

39:13.046 --> 39:14.345
This is a dream come true.

39:14.346 --> 39:16.179
It's like
I'm dreaming right now.

39:16.180 --> 39:18.745
Like, wow.
[cheers and applause]

39:18.746 --> 39:22.412
[gentle music]

39:22.413 --> 39:25.079
We are from
a small community

39:25.080 --> 39:28.445
in Limpopo, South Africa,

39:28.446 --> 39:31.079
and there's a lot
of difficulties there.

39:31.080 --> 39:34.679
Growing up, it has been
really hard for us.

39:34.680 --> 39:38.045
The place,
it has a lot of poverty.

39:38.046 --> 39:40.679
Many places have
no electricity,

39:40.680 --> 39:43.445
and most of the homes
do not have running water.

39:43.446 --> 39:46.312
It's very difficult.

39:46.313 --> 39:49.245
The challenges
these kids face,

39:49.246 --> 39:51.479
it's devastating.

39:51.480 --> 39:54.545
Many of our kids' parents
have passed away,

39:54.546 --> 39:55.812
and they've got to look after

39:55.813 --> 39:57.712
their little siblings
on their own.

39:57.713 --> 39:59.879
So to try and help
those orphans

39:59.880 --> 40:04.045
and vulnerable children,
we started the choir.

40:04.046 --> 40:06.412
My father passed away
two years ago.

40:06.413 --> 40:09.045
Everything changed.

40:09.046 --> 40:10.779
[sniffles]

40:10.780 --> 40:13.812
It was very difficult,

40:13.813 --> 40:16.945
and I had to take care

40:16.946 --> 40:20.480
of all of us and...

40:29.213 --> 40:31.845
When they join us,
many of our kids

40:31.846 --> 40:34.279
have the weight of the world
on their shoulders,

40:34.280 --> 40:39.312
and to them, their problems
feel insurmountable.

40:39.313 --> 40:41.579
For us,
it's not easy to dream,

40:41.580 --> 40:44.579
so I didn't like to smile,

40:44.580 --> 40:47.045
but after joining the choir,

40:47.046 --> 40:49.745
I found my voice

40:49.746 --> 40:53.879
and it brought back
the smile on my face.

40:53.880 --> 40:55.879
♪ ♪

40:55.880 --> 40:57.245
Being in the choir,

40:57.246 --> 40:59.745
it just gave me
a sense of belonging

40:59.746 --> 41:02.112
and confidence
to not be afraid,

41:02.113 --> 41:03.745
that it's okay to dream,

41:03.746 --> 41:05.479
so you just know
the sky is the limit.

41:05.480 --> 41:09.545
Exactly, that's why now we
want to show the whole world

41:09.546 --> 41:12.246
that anything is possible.

41:13.713 --> 41:15.579
They come from one
of the poorest communities

41:15.580 --> 41:18.345
in the world,
yet these kids manage

41:18.346 --> 41:20.912
to lift themselves up.

41:20.913 --> 41:22.679
To see them standing
on the stage

41:22.680 --> 41:26.746
of "America's Got Talent"
tonight, I just--

41:28.580 --> 41:31.479
Sorry.

41:31.480 --> 41:33.813
[chuckles] That was--

41:43.313 --> 41:46.945
You can't help but just
burst with pride.

41:46.946 --> 41:49.345
[cheers and applause]

41:49.346 --> 41:51.679
Can you tell me the song?

41:51.680 --> 41:53.545
Is it original?
What's it about?

41:53.546 --> 41:56.479
So the song that we're
gonna sing for you today

41:56.480 --> 41:58.379
is called "My African Dream."

41:58.380 --> 41:59.812
Couldn't be more perfect
for today,

41:59.813 --> 42:02.345
because it expresses
hopes and dreams,

42:02.346 --> 42:05.712
and our dream is to let
children around the world

42:05.713 --> 42:08.512
know that just because
you're born in poverty,

42:08.513 --> 42:10.645
it doesn't mean that
you are poverty.

42:10.646 --> 42:14.579
[cheers and applause]
That's beautiful.

42:14.580 --> 42:16.445
All right, well,
that's pretty exciting.

42:16.446 --> 42:18.745
You've come all the way
from South Africa,

42:18.746 --> 42:21.045
and you are now on
the biggest talent stage

42:21.046 --> 42:22.912
in the world,
so I can't wait to hear

42:22.913 --> 42:24.445
what it is you do.

42:24.446 --> 42:25.612
Good.
Thank you.

42:25.613 --> 42:27.280
[cheers and applause]

42:41.580 --> 42:44.212
["My African Dream" begins]

42:44.213 --> 42:47.579
[vocalizing indistinctly]

42:47.580 --> 42:50.512
♪ In my Africa ♪

42:50.513 --> 42:54.512
♪ Sometimes alone
in the evening ♪

42:54.513 --> 42:57.145
♪ I look outside my window ♪

42:57.146 --> 43:00.812
♪ At the shadow in the night ♪

43:00.813 --> 43:02.779
[all chanting]

43:02.780 --> 43:05.412
♪ I hear the sound
of distant crying ♪

43:05.413 --> 43:08.512
♪ The darkness multiplying ♪

43:08.513 --> 43:14.012
♪ The weary hearts denied ♪

43:14.013 --> 43:17.545
♪ All I hear are the voices ♪

43:17.546 --> 43:20.379
♪ Telling me to go ♪

43:20.380 --> 43:25.579
♪ But I could never run ♪

43:25.580 --> 43:27.945
[all chanting
in native language]

43:27.946 --> 43:30.945
♪ In my African dream ♪

43:30.946 --> 43:35.045
[all singing
in native language]

43:35.046 --> 43:38.045
♪ There's a new tomorrow ♪

43:38.046 --> 43:40.379
[all singing
in native language]

43:40.380 --> 43:42.912
♪ My African dreams ♪

43:42.913 --> 43:45.879
[all singing
in native language]

43:45.880 --> 43:51.512
♪ Is the dream
that we can follow ♪

43:51.513 --> 43:53.445
[vocalizing]

43:53.446 --> 43:55.545
[all singing
in native language]

43:55.546 --> 44:02.613
♪ ♪

44:14.846 --> 44:17.512
♪ This is ♪

44:17.513 --> 44:20.545
♪ My African ♪

44:20.546 --> 44:22.812
♪ Yeah-yeah-yeah ♪

44:22.813 --> 44:24.712
♪ Dream ♪

44:24.713 --> 44:27.012
♪ Oh yeah, yeah ♪

44:27.013 --> 44:29.845
[singing crescendos]

44:29.846 --> 44:32.080
[wild cheering]

44:34.146 --> 44:41.045
["True Colors" plays]

44:41.046 --> 44:42.913
Whoo!

44:48.813 --> 44:51.046
Wow.

44:54.246 --> 44:57.245
Gabrielle?

44:57.246 --> 44:58.812
From the second
you walked out,

44:58.813 --> 45:00.679
I think this whole place
was rooting for you,

45:00.680 --> 45:02.479
and you did not disappoint.

45:02.480 --> 45:04.312
[cheers and applause]

45:04.313 --> 45:08.312
You showcased the beauty
that you represent,

45:08.313 --> 45:10.012
and you are giving
so much hope.

45:10.013 --> 45:13.145
I can't thank you enough.
Thank you.

45:13.146 --> 45:16.279
Julianne.
Oh!

45:16.280 --> 45:20.445
To feel your authenticity
and joy just coming through,

45:20.446 --> 45:23.712
I felt like you transported us
to where you're from,

45:23.713 --> 45:26.112
and it was so beautiful,
so magical.

45:26.113 --> 45:27.845
Well done.
Thank you.

45:27.846 --> 45:29.745
[cheers and applause]

45:29.746 --> 45:31.945
There's nothing
more exciting than when

45:31.946 --> 45:35.045
people come from far away
to this stage,

45:35.046 --> 45:37.345
and you bring your culture,
and you bring your life

45:37.346 --> 45:38.912
and share your talent.

45:38.913 --> 45:40.979
And everything you did,
from how you're dressed--

45:40.980 --> 45:43.512
I mean, I love the color,
and I love the sound.

45:43.513 --> 45:45.179
I really do.
Thank you.

45:45.180 --> 45:47.745
Simon?

45:47.746 --> 45:50.612
You know, we've always been
waiting for a choir like this,

45:50.613 --> 45:52.979
something we've
never heard before,

45:52.980 --> 45:55.212
and your energy
was just literally

45:55.213 --> 45:57.379
bouncing off me right there.

45:57.380 --> 45:59.012
[cheers and applause]

45:59.013 --> 46:02.145
It was a great audition,
and you I'm going to remember.

46:02.146 --> 46:04.345
Well done.
Thank you.

46:04.346 --> 46:06.612
Let's vote.
Gabrielle.

46:06.613 --> 46:09.079
It's a thousand times
yes for me.

46:09.080 --> 46:10.745
Julianne?

46:10.746 --> 46:12.479
Yes! Whoo!

46:12.480 --> 46:14.945
Simon?
I'm gonna say yes.

46:14.946 --> 46:17.112
It's four yeses.

46:17.113 --> 46:20.712
♪ True colors
shining through ♪

46:20.713 --> 46:22.212
♪ See 'em shining through ♪

46:22.213 --> 46:24.779
♪ Your true colors ♪

46:24.780 --> 46:28.312
[all chanting, cheering]

46:28.313 --> 46:30.612
♪ Don't be afraid ♪

46:30.613 --> 46:32.879
♪ To let them show ♪

46:32.880 --> 46:34.979
♪ Your true colors ♪

46:34.980 --> 46:38.245
This goes out to all the kids
in South Africa and Africa,

46:38.246 --> 46:39.945
everyone that has the dream--

46:39.946 --> 46:41.345
We are shooting
for the stars.

46:41.346 --> 46:42.745
Yes, yes!
[all cheering]

46:42.746 --> 46:47.846
♪ Beautiful like a rainbow ♪

46:52.313 --> 46:52.346
.

46:53.713 --> 46:54.080
[cheers and applause]

46:54.613 --> 46:56.645
all: Howie! Howie! Howie!

46:56.646 --> 46:58.212
You know what
gets me moving?

46:58.213 --> 47:00.145
Running through
a few thousand strangers

47:00.146 --> 47:02.045
who haven't washed
their hands in an hour.

47:02.046 --> 47:03.712
[chuckles]
You'll get me moving.

47:03.713 --> 47:06.145
Everybody's got an open palm,
and they just want to touch.

47:06.146 --> 47:07.479
That is, like,
your worst nightmare.

47:07.480 --> 47:08.645
This is a Petri dish.

47:08.646 --> 47:13.779
Look but don't touch
for Howie Mandel.

47:13.780 --> 47:15.812
♪ Music so hard ♪

47:15.813 --> 47:17.645
♪ Makes me say oh my lord ♪

47:17.646 --> 47:19.545
♪ Thank you for blessing me ♪

47:19.546 --> 47:21.379
♪ With a mind to rhyme
and two hype feet ♪

47:21.380 --> 47:23.179
♪ That's good
when you know you're down ♪

47:23.180 --> 47:25.412
My man, Howie Mandel.
Yes.

47:25.413 --> 47:27.912
How are you feeling?
Oh, I'll tell you.

47:27.913 --> 47:29.679
For somebody that doesn't
want to touch hands,

47:29.680 --> 47:31.912
just to be here,
it's amazing.

47:31.913 --> 47:33.079
[laughter]

47:33.080 --> 47:34.312
You know,
to be honest with you,

47:34.313 --> 47:37.412
I am scared to death
of everything

47:37.413 --> 47:39.379
every minute of my life.
♪ Can't touch ♪

47:39.380 --> 47:42.545
I am Simone.
And I am Lorenzo.

47:42.546 --> 47:46.179
And we are the creators
of Idego Virtual Reality.

47:46.180 --> 47:47.712
[lively classical music]

47:47.713 --> 47:51.412
All of the world,
everyone is sitting on fears,

47:51.413 --> 47:53.845
phobias, like arachnophobia,

47:53.846 --> 47:55.845
fear of flying,
fear of heights.

47:55.846 --> 47:58.212
They get up,
they go to work,

47:58.213 --> 47:59.679
but they are living a life

47:59.680 --> 48:03.512
that stops them from achieving
their potential.

48:03.513 --> 48:04.845
♪ ♪

48:04.846 --> 48:07.279
We developed virtual
reality technology,

48:07.280 --> 48:09.579
and with this tool
people discover

48:09.580 --> 48:13.045
that they are capable of things
that they have never imagined.

48:13.046 --> 48:16.679
This is our opportunity
to share this potential

48:16.680 --> 48:18.245
with the entire world.

48:18.246 --> 48:20.745
[cheers and applause]

48:20.746 --> 48:22.945
♪ ♪

48:22.946 --> 48:24.645
Hello.
What's your name?

48:24.646 --> 48:27.079
My name is Simone.
And my name is Lorenzo.

48:27.080 --> 48:30.079
Where are you from?
Rome, Italy.

48:30.080 --> 48:32.445
And what do you guys
do in Rome?

48:32.446 --> 48:34.445
We are psychologists.
Oh.

48:34.446 --> 48:37.645
And we love technology,
so we wanted to find a way

48:37.646 --> 48:40.545
to put technology
and psychology together,

48:40.546 --> 48:42.745
so we created this
virtual reality software

48:42.746 --> 48:43.879
for the mental health.

48:43.880 --> 48:46.145
So cool.
I love that.

48:46.146 --> 48:47.845
I don't know if you know
who you're talking to,

48:47.846 --> 48:51.045
but in this country,
I've put a lot of psychologists

48:51.046 --> 48:52.545
into a whole new tax bracket.

48:52.546 --> 48:54.345
[laughter]

48:54.346 --> 48:56.279
So why "AGT"?

48:56.280 --> 49:00.279
We often say when a person
overcomes phobias,

49:00.280 --> 49:03.545
that person is actually
finding his own talent.

49:03.546 --> 49:06.012
So our talent
is to help others

49:06.013 --> 49:08.145
unlocking their talent.

49:08.146 --> 49:10.279
Whoo! Love that.
Wow.

49:10.280 --> 49:12.379
So I would like
to invite you onstage.

49:12.380 --> 49:13.745
[cheers and applause]

49:13.746 --> 49:16.079
Oh, "you," meaning me?
Yeah, you.

49:16.080 --> 49:17.945
Whoo! Yes!

49:17.946 --> 49:20.779
So we're going to put you
in a virtual situation

49:20.780 --> 49:23.679
where you're going to find out
that you're capable of things

49:23.680 --> 49:25.112
you didn't know you could do.

49:25.113 --> 49:26.545
Oh, wow.

49:26.546 --> 49:28.246
[cheers and applause]

49:33.980 --> 49:35.880
Come with me.
All right.

49:36.980 --> 49:39.779
[cheers and applause]

49:39.780 --> 49:41.779
I--I--
Oh, sorry, sorry.

49:41.780 --> 49:43.179
You found my first phobia.
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

49:43.180 --> 49:44.512
[laughter]

49:44.513 --> 49:46.979
First of all, we are
going to take off our shoes

49:46.980 --> 49:49.446
to get on the green, okay?
Okay.

49:50.546 --> 49:52.445
So come with me.
All right.

49:52.446 --> 49:53.779
Don't be scared.
Just trust me.

49:53.780 --> 49:55.812
Too late.
[laughter]

49:55.813 --> 49:59.679
So do you prefer to put on
the headset by yourself?

49:59.680 --> 50:01.312
Yeah.
Okay.

50:01.313 --> 50:03.212
I could--I'm a big boy.

50:03.213 --> 50:05.445
Okay.
[laughter]

50:05.446 --> 50:07.179
And put it on?
Yeah, put it on.

50:07.180 --> 50:08.612
Okay.
[coyote howls]

50:08.613 --> 50:10.512
Oh.
What do you see?

50:10.513 --> 50:13.745
I'm not in a fun place.
[laughter]

50:13.746 --> 50:16.379
I see somebody
in more trouble than me,

50:16.380 --> 50:19.645
and a bird,
and I'm in a canyon,

50:19.646 --> 50:22.245
and I don't--you know, I don't
know if I told you this,

50:22.246 --> 50:24.012
heights is one of my phobias.

50:24.013 --> 50:27.045
Yes, that's why
you're here with us.

50:27.046 --> 50:29.279
The balloon.
[laughs]

50:29.280 --> 50:31.579
Now, walking on the ropes,

50:31.580 --> 50:34.445
your aim is to save
that person

50:34.446 --> 50:36.379
whose life is in danger.

50:36.380 --> 50:38.479
All right.
Are you ready?

50:38.480 --> 50:40.212
Howie!
[cheers and applause]

50:40.213 --> 50:42.679
Please, Howie.
Okay.

50:42.680 --> 50:44.912
All right, I'll try.
I don't like this.

50:44.913 --> 50:47.745
Be very careful where
you place your feet.

50:47.746 --> 50:50.612
I'm trying to, but I don't--
I don't--I don't--

50:50.613 --> 50:53.445
Oh, my gosh.
Just a little bit like this.

50:53.446 --> 50:55.979
Okay, okay, you can do it.
I can't, I can't.

50:55.980 --> 50:57.912
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
you can do it.

50:57.913 --> 51:00.812
I can't, I can't.
Okay, okay.

51:00.813 --> 51:02.645
Julianne.
Oh, my gosh.

51:02.646 --> 51:05.579
We are going to do
the first step together,

51:05.580 --> 51:09.012
and then you'll be able
to go on by yourself, okay?

51:09.013 --> 51:11.512
Yeah.
Can't he come and save me?

51:11.513 --> 51:13.079
[laughter]

51:13.080 --> 51:14.245
[light music]

51:14.246 --> 51:15.812
Oh, my Gosh. Oh.
Okay, okay.

51:15.813 --> 51:18.845
You got it, Howie!
I can't.

51:18.846 --> 51:20.812
Go, Howie!
[cheers and applause]

51:20.813 --> 51:22.745
Can I crawl?

51:22.746 --> 51:24.145
No, don't do like this.
Why?

51:24.146 --> 51:25.912
Don't do like this.
It's worse.

51:25.913 --> 51:29.679
You're gonna fall.
I can't--I'm too scared.

51:29.680 --> 51:32.079
♪ ♪

51:32.080 --> 51:34.312
[cheers and applause]

51:34.313 --> 51:36.279
♪ ♪

51:36.280 --> 51:37.412
[laughter]

51:37.413 --> 51:38.612
There you go, Howie.

51:38.613 --> 51:41.179
I'm too scared.

51:41.180 --> 51:42.512
What do I do now?

51:42.513 --> 51:44.145
Grab his arm.
You have to save him.

51:44.146 --> 51:45.779
What?
Grab his arm.

51:45.780 --> 51:48.079
You have to save him.
Grab his arm?

51:48.080 --> 51:51.312
Arm, yeah, the arm.
I don't touch people's hands!

51:51.313 --> 51:52.913
[laughter and applause]

51:54.913 --> 51:56.112
He's gonna fall.

51:56.113 --> 51:58.145
Can't I just go
and save myself?

51:58.146 --> 52:00.512
Push your limit.
Come on, Howie.

52:00.513 --> 52:01.979
You can do it.
Oh, my gosh.

52:01.980 --> 52:04.079
Come on, Howie!
How do I get him?

52:04.080 --> 52:06.812
I can't get--
oh, I feel him.

52:06.813 --> 52:10.245
[cheers and applause]

52:10.246 --> 52:11.479
Now save him.
Save him.

52:11.480 --> 52:13.812
Okay. Okay.

52:13.813 --> 52:17.845
♪ ♪

52:17.846 --> 52:19.345
You did it.
I'm a hero.

52:19.346 --> 52:20.879
Yeah!

52:20.880 --> 52:23.345
♪ ♪

52:23.346 --> 52:25.345
Who are you?
[laughter]

52:25.346 --> 52:27.279
[cheers and applause]

52:27.280 --> 52:28.479
Yay!

52:28.480 --> 52:32.179
[The Script's "Hall of Fame"]

52:32.180 --> 52:34.645
He faced his fear.
That was amazing.

52:34.646 --> 52:37.679
♪ ♪

52:37.680 --> 52:40.479
all: Howie! Howie! Howie!

52:40.480 --> 52:42.679
Howie! Howie! Howie!

52:42.680 --> 52:45.812
Oh, my--that's terrifying.
Okey dokey.

52:45.813 --> 52:47.312
Oh.
Wow.

52:47.313 --> 52:49.479
Howie, how do you feel
right now?

52:49.480 --> 52:50.745
I feel like a hero.

52:50.746 --> 52:53.545
♪ Standing in
the hall of fame ♪

52:53.546 --> 52:55.012
Yeah!

52:55.013 --> 52:57.679
I'll be honest with you,
I was terrified,

52:57.680 --> 53:00.312
